{
  "_doc": "Marvel's Spider-Man (code SPM) — Universes Beyond set. Source: https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-marvels-spider-man . Lineup is Play Boosters + Collector Boosters only (no Draft). Percentages taken verbatim from the article's odds tables. Approximations: the article cites separate printings (SPE 'Welcome Deck' reprints, scene cards, source material, web-slinger / panel / classic-comic Booster Fun frames, textured-foil costume-change, borderless Gauntlet Soul Stone, textless cosmic-foil Soul Stone) that have no dedicated Scryfall sub-set code we model, so they are approximated against the main SPM pool with the nearest available filter: web-slinger/panel/scene/classic-comic -> 'showcase', extended-art -> 'extended_art', borderless/source-material chases -> 'borderless'. The borderless costume-change cards are a specifically-named premium finish, so that chase is targeted exactly via promo_types -> 'textured_foil' instead of the 'borderless' stand-in. The textless 'cosmic foil' Soul Stone stays on 'serialized' as a quantity stand-in — Scryfall's cosmic-foil promo_type has no dedicated filter here and is NOT the same as galaxy_foil, so it is left as-is. The borderless Gauntlet Soul Stone appears only in traditional foil (no named premium finish) so it stays 'borderless'. Sub-percentages reported as 'less than 1%' are entered as 0.5; the 'extremely low quantity' serialized Soul Stone is 0.1. AUDIT 2026-06: two filter mappings upgraded after the recipe audit found them matching zero cards: (1) scene-card outcomes moved from the 'showcase' stand-in to 'scene_card' (promo_types:poster — the actual Scryfall tag; scene commons/uncommons never carry the showcase frame effect, so those outcomes silently re-rolled); (2) Source Material outcomes moved from 'borderless on SPM' to the exact sheet: set MAR (Marvel Universe) + 'spm_source_material' (collector 1-40 — the SPM-era half; 41-100 belong to MSH). Web-slinger / panel / classic-comic stay on 'showcase' (they genuinely carry that frame effect). Gold-stamped art cards keep their outcome even though Scryfall doesn't model the stamp as a separate print — it falls through to a plain art card by design. AUDIT 2026-06: special-finish outcome rarities corrected to match the actual printed sheets (pool-verified): textured_foil->rare. AUDIT 2026-06 part 3: scene outcomes at rarity:uncommon dropped their rarity constraint — SPM scene (poster) prints file at rare/mythic on Scryfall regardless of the article’s slot framing, so the constraint emptied the outcome.",
